As political contest for baton change hots up in Osun state, the former head of service in Osun State, Elder Olusegun Akinwusi has extolled the leadership qualities of Dr. Akin Ogunbiyi, saying that the latter has the magic wand to turn-around the fortunes of the state. Dr. Akin Ogunbiyi, a frontline politician and gubernatorial candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in the forthcoming primary election is the Chairman/Founder of Mutual Benefits Assurance Plc and a major investor across industries locally and globally. C ommenting on the gubernatorial aspiration of Dr. Ogunbiyi, the former head of service, an astute bureaucrat and community leader disclosed that the gubernatorial candidate has all it takes to improve the fortunes of the state by leading it on the path of quick economic growth and development. 2022 IWD: NGO To Gift 100 Traders, Street Sweepers Food Items 2023: Hope Alive As Gov Emmanuel Reviews Ongoing Projects In… Elder Akinwusi stated that the responsibilities attached to the position of the governor of a state can only be efficiently carried out by Dr. Akin Ogunbiyi who also currently sits as the Group Chairman of Mutual Benefits Assurance PLC, a Conglomerate of nine subsidiaries with over 5,000 employees. He stated: “It is only Dr Akin Ogunbiyi out of all the governorship aspirants that can rejuvenate the decaying and dying economy and social services of Osun State. We do not need a Governor in Osun who will depend on statutory allocation all the time but one who will substantially grow internally generated revenue and introduce innovative ideas and strategies to develop Osun State from its present decaying state.”